data.value: Add sent line/byte to console output window.

data.name: cbHexRead.ToolTip
data.value: Present received data in hex format

data.name: cbC40bDR.ToolTip
data.value: Add extra shift clock cycles every 64 pixel for dual-panel LCD. 0 = No extra shift clock cycles 1 = Add extra shift clock cycles

data.name: cbC40bTL.ToolTip
data.value: Select TV or LCD mode (apply to SED1336): 0 = LCD mode (keep 0 for SED1330/1335) 1 = TV mode (enabled TV circuits)

data.name: cbC40bIV.ToolTip
data.value: Screen orgin compenstation for inverse display. 0 = screen top-line correction 1 = No screen top-line correction

data.name: cbC40bWS.ToolTip
data.value: Single or dual panel configuration: 0 = Single-panel 1 = Dual-panel

data.name: cbC40bM2.ToolTip
data.value: Select height of CR ROM && CG RAM char height: 0 = 8px 1 = 16px

data.name: cbC40bM1.ToolTip
data.value: Select CG RAM area for custom characters. 0 = 32 char CG RAM1 1 = 64 char CG RAM + CG RAM2

data.name: cbC40bM0.ToolTip
data.value: Select CG ROM source: 0 = Internal CG ROM 1 = External CG ROM

data.name: cbC40bWF.ToolTip
data.value: Select the AC frame drive waveform period. 0 = 16-line AC drive 1 = two-frame AC drive

data.name: eC40FX.ToolTip
data.value: Set the character width in pixels: FX+1

data.name: eC40CR.ToolTip
data.value: Bytes per display lines minus one.

data.name: eC40TCR.ToolTip
data.value: Set the line length incl. horizontal blankingm of one line. Line length equal TC/R+1. Must be >= (C/R+4).

data.name: eC40LF.ToolTip
data.value: Height in lines of frame. Real height is: L/F+1. In case of dual-panel driving (W/S=1), L/F must be odd value.

data.name: eC40AP.ToolTip
data.value: Horizontal address range of virtual screen. (0..65535)

data.name: eC44SL1SL2.ToolTip
data.value: SL1 && SL2 is equal (3-layer config). Set the number of lines per scrolling screen.

data.name: eC5AD2_0.ToolTip
data.value: Scroll screen in X-dir by pixels.

data.name: bDispDoMath.ToolTip
data.value: Do some math on entered parameters of LCD && config

data.name: eSEDFFR.ToolTip
data.value: Desired refresh frame rate in Hz
